<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2004-10-05</DATELINE><TITLE>Sea Turtles: Old Viruses and New Tricks</TITLE><BODY>Abstract Recent years have seen an inexplicable increase in the frequency of an appalling disease in sea turtles: fibropapillomatosis, which is likely caused by a herpesvirus and causes tumors to grow throughout the turtle's body. New research has led to the disturbing conclusion that recent, human-induced environmental changes are responsible.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>